I'm new to Tindi and I'll be the first to say half the guild has more pride than it knows what to do with (Example: this here thread!) BUT FFS how hard is Everquest? Where are the random encounters and thinking AI? Right, it's not hard, it's seamlessly predictable (well, AE charm is sorta teh suck). The challenge lies in making people work together smoothly, not figuring out leet strats to beat mobs. That's what created the CH chain way the fuck back in the day. &quot;OMFG if you guys all CH me every 2 seconds in a perfect chain I'll never die! unless he flurries, hmm....&quot;<br>
